From: Eric Dumazet <eric.dumazet@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 19 Oct 2011 23:00:23 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 08/15] bnx2x: fix skb truesize underestimation

Git-commit: e1ac50f64691de9a095ac5d73cb8ac73d3d17dba
Patch-mainline: v3.1-rc11? merged into net-next
References: bnc#709064

bnx2x allocates a full page per fragment.

We must account in skb->truesize, the size of the fragment, not the used
part of it.

Signed-off-by: Eric Dumazet <eric.dumazet@gmail.com>
CC: Eilon Greenstein <eilong@broadcom.com>
Acked-by: Lee, Chun-Yi <jlee@suse.com>
---
 drivers/net/bnx2x/bnx2x_cmn.c |    2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/drivers/net/bnx2x/bnx2x_cmn.c
+++ b/drivers/net/bnx2x/bnx2x_cmn.c
@@ -451,7 +451,7 @@ static int bnx2x_fill_frag_skb(struct bn
 		skb_fill_page_desc(skb, j, old_rx_pg.page, 0, frag_len);
 
 		skb->data_len += frag_len;
-		skb->truesize += frag_len;
+		skb->truesize += SGE_PAGE_SIZE * PAGES_PER_SGE;
 		skb->len += frag_len;
 
 		frag_size -= frag_len;
